.Python
# Anchored to the repo root (leading /) - Python packaging-artifact dir
# names like "lib" are common, ordinary directory names in JS/TS projects
# too. An unanchored `lib/` here previously matched frontend/src/lib/ as
# well as any Python build/ dist/ output, silently keeping api.ts and
# utils.ts out of git entirely (confirmed via `git log` showing zero
# history for either file) - a fresh clone would be missing files nearly
# every frontend page imports, and the frontend Docker build would fail.
/build/
/develop-eggs/
/dist/
/downloads/
/eggs/
.eggs/
/lib/
/lib64/
/parts/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
/sdist/
/var/
/wheels/
/share/python-wheels/
*.egg-info/
.installed.cfg
*.egg
